owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The location where the Connector is physically deployed.

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Provider of a Resource or Service that is the subject matter of the contract. This party may differ from the Assigner specified by the Contract rules.

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Named spatial entity covered by the Resource.

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Route between two or more app endpoints inside a app routing pipeline.

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Temporal period or instance covered by the content.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: URL reference to a custom license regulating the general usage of the Resource.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Indicates the data type of the Representation.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: IRI reference to a documentation of the endpoint, e.g., reference to an OpenAPI-based documentation.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Reference to SHACL shape graph, which describes domain-specific knowledge.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: shapeGraph

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Indicates an address for the site.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: site address

License IRI should refer to the direct of link for a given standard license, e.g., MIT license (https://www.wikidata.org/wiki/Q334661). The label of the resolved wikidata license IRI can be used to present the license in human-readable form.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: title

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: An authentication token value like JSON Web Token.

In order to prevent these attacks, a binding of this transport certificates to the connector is required. The inclusion of SHA256 fingerprints of currently valid transport certificates, mainly into the DAT, enables the client to relate the transport layer security with the IDS interactions.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: transportCertsSha256

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: URI of the trust store server.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: trust store

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Version identifier of the Managed Entity
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: version

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Width of the visible frame.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: width

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The upper class of Constraints and LogicalConstraints is solely intended as a placholder at the range of IDS Properties.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Abstract Constraint

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Message requesting an access token. This is intended for point-to-point communication with, e.g., Brokers.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: AccessToken Request Message

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Response to an access token request, intended for point-to-point communication.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Access Token Response

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A thing one might be permitted to do or prohibited from doing to something.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Action

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Internal or external Agent interacting with the Industrial Data Space, not necessarily an IDS Participant.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Agent

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Message indicating that a specific App should be available (again) in the AppStore.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: App Available Message

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Message indicating that an App should be deleted from the AppStore.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: App Delete Message

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Description of endpoints a DataApp offers.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: DataApp Endpoint

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Class of endpoint types a data app offers.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: App endpoint type

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Resource control for deployed services.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: App execution resources

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Superclass of all messages, indicating a change of a DataApp. Unlike Resource-related Messages, AppNotificationMessages should lead to a state change for an app at the recipient, the AppStore.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: App Notification Message

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Message that asks for registration or update of a data app to the App Store. Payload contains app-related metadata (instance of class ids:AppResource). Message header may contain an app identifier parameter of a prior registered data app. If the app identifier is supplied, the message should be interpreted as a registration for an app update. Otherwise this message is used to register a new app.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: App Registration Request Message

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Message that follows up an AppRegistrationRequestMessage and contains the app registration confimation.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: App Registration Response Message

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: App representation
owl:Class.rdfs:label: App Representation

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Resource comprising IDS data apps.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: App Resource

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: ids:AppRoute describes the communication between data apps (such as in a data processing pipeline) inside an IDS Connector. An ids:AppRoute consist of multiple app endpoints which exchange data. The communication pipeline between data apps is represented by the ids:EndToEndRoutes class. ids:AppRoute also holds the information about the app endpoints, which are at the start and end of the whole processing pipeline.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: App Route

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Secure platform for distributing Data Apps.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: App Store

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Message indicating that a specific App should be unavailable in the AppStore.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: App Unavailable Message

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Message that usually follows a AppRegistrationResponseMessage and is used to upload a data app to the app store. Payload contains data app. Note that the message must refer to the prior sent, corresponding AppResource instance. The IRI of the ids:appArtifactReference must must match the IRI of the artifact which is the value for the ids:instance property. The ids:instance is specific for each representation. Therefore, if someone wants to upload multiple representations for an app, he has to state them using multiple ids:instance properties inside the AppRepresentation (and therefore inside the AppResource). Otherwise no mapping between payload and app metadata can be achieved.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: App Upload Message

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Message that follows up an AppUploadMessage and contains the app upload confimation.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: App Upload Response Message

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Instance of a Representation materialized at a partiuclar version and point in time. Possesses characteristics like file name, size, creation date etc.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Artifact

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Message asking for retrieving the specified Artifact as the payload of an ArtifactResponse message.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Artifact Request Message

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Message that follows up a RetrieveArtifact Message and contains the Artifact's data in the payload section.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Artifact Response Message

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The state which an ids:Artifact may have or not.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Artifact State

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: An Asset is either an ids:Resource, an ids:Representation, or an ids:Artifact. The Asset is used to reference the target of an ids:Contract.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Asset

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: An AssetCollection is a bracket object combining several ids:Assets.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Asset Collection

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The class of audiences (recipients) used in the JWT.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Audience

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Audio representation
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Audio Representation

As a direct consequence of regarding the DAT Payload as JSON-LD, *all* DAT Payloads must have exactly one "@context" attribute with the IDS context URI as its value and a "@type" with ids:DatPayload as its value.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: DAT Payload

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The Dynamic Attribute Token (DAT) *Request* Payload is the JSON Element of any DAT containing the claims of the token bearer. This payload itself is a JSON-LD encoded RDF class with a defined set of attributes. These attributes are either defined by RFC 7519 or by the IDS Information Model. As a direct consequence of regarding the DAT Payload as JSON-LD, *all* DAT Payloads must have exactly one "@context" attribute with the IDS context URI as its value and a "@type" with ids:DatPayload as its value. Note that, different to the DatPayload, the DatRequestPayload contains the *self-claims* of a connector and is not yet signed by any DAPS. Consequently, no other connector must accept a DatRequest object as a DAT. A DatRequest and its contained DatRequestPayload is *only* intended for interactions with a DAPS and *nothing else*!
owl:Class.rdfs:label: DAT Request Payload

In case the connector only appears as a virtual entity, the physical location of the hosting server is referenced. Allowed operators are idsc:in. No other spatial operators (close to, north of, etc.) are currently allowed.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Absolute geo-spatial position

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: If a temporal entity T1 is after another temporal entity T2, then the beginning of T1 is after the end of T2 and the beginning of T1 is different to the ending of T2. Temporal entities can either be a xsd:dateTimeStamp or an ids:TemporalEntity.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: after

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Data will be part of another piece of data so that it is not distinguishable anymore.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: aggregate by consumer

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Data will be part of another piece of data so that it is not distinguishable anymore.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: aggregate by provider
owl:NamedIndividual.skos:note: This action is always evaluated at the provider side.

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: The event occurs once a year.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Annual

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: To anonymize all, parts or certain attributes of the resource.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: anonymize
owl:NamedIndividual.skos:note: This action is always evaluated at the provider side.

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: The artifact is anonymized so the data source can not be recognized by any further user.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: is anonymized

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: At least one query or operation parameter is not acceptable for the sender of this rejection message.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: BAD_PARAMETERS

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Default security profile of a certified IDS Connector.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Base security profile

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: If a temporal entity T1 is before another temporal entity T2, then the ending of T1 is before the end of T2 and the ending of T1 is different to the beginning of T2. Temporal entities can either be a xsd:dateTimeStamp or an ids:TemporalEntity.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: before
owl:NamedIndividual.skos:note: Compares an instance of ids:TemporalEntity or a Literal of xsd:dateTimeStamp to an instance of ids:TemporalEntity or a Literal of xsd:dateTimeStamp.

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: The event occurs every two years.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Biennial

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: The event occurs every two months.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Bimonthly

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: The event occurs every two weeks.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Biweekly

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: The artifact is a collection of smaller artifacts and can be split into parts when necessary.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: is combined

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: To pay a certain amount of money in order to use a resource.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: compensate
owl:NamedIndividual.skos:note: This action must be evaluated both at the consumer and provider side. A compensation might be required before access is granted (provider-side), or each time the usage action is performed (consumer-side).

Base Security Profile Certification of Components based on Concept Review

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Config endpoint

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Indicates that a Connector is badly configured.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Connector badly configured

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Indicates that a Connector is offline.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Connector Offline

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Indicates that a Connector is online.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Connector Online

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: If a TemporalEntity (or xsd:dateTimeStamp) T1 contains another ids:TemporalEntity T2, then the beginning of T1 is idsc:AFTER the beginning of T2 and the ending of T1 is idsc:BEFORE the ending of T2. An Instant (or xsd:dateTimeStamp) cannot contain another Instant (or xsd:dateTimeStamp), neihter contains itself.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: contains
owl:NamedIndividual.skos:note: Compares an instance of ids:Instant, ids:Interval or xsd:dateTimeStamp with an instance of ids:Interval. Evaluates to false if compared to a non ids:Interval.

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: The event repeats without interruption.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Continuous

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Numeric count of executions of the Rule. Operators can be idsc:LT, idsc:LTEQ, idsc:EQ, idsc:GT, idsc:GTEQ. Datatype is xsd:double.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: count

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Spatial operator 'covered by' as defined by the Egenhofer Topological Relations family: An object A is covered_by another object B if both objects share common bounding and interior faces; if A has interior faces which are bounding faces of B; and if none of B's interior faces are part of A's boundary. (https://doi.org/10.1007/3-540-51295-0_148 Definition 7)
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: covered by

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Spatial operator 'covers' as defined by the Egenhofer Topological Relations family: An object A covers another object B if both objects share common bounding and interior faces; if B has interior faces which are bounding faces of A; and if none of A's interior faces are part of B's boundary. (https://doi.org/10.1007/3-540-51295-0_148 Definition 6)
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: covers
Old Church Slavonic, Church Slavonic, Old Bulgarian

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: The event occurs once a day.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Daily

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Debug level logging.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Debug Level Logging

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Allows assignments similar to 'var x := {RightOperand}'.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: defines as
owl:NamedIndividual.skos:note: Different to the other ids:BinaryOperator, idsc:DEFINES_AS does *not* compare a feature but tells the interpreter where to *find* one. Therefore, the constraint is not evaluated in the same way as with other operators.

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Delay the action. Use idsc:DURATION_EQ, idsc:LONGER, idsc:LONGER_EQ, idsc:SHORTER_EQ, or idsc:SHORTER with datatype xsd:duration.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: delay

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: To remove a resource or inhibit any further access with reasonable measures.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: delete
owl:NamedIndividual.skos:note: This action is evaluated at the consumer side if used in a duty clause. A provider cannot be forced to delete its data resources. If used in a permission clause, it is effecting the data provider as it allows the consumer to delete the provider's resource remotely.

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Spatial operator 'disjoint' as defined by the Egenhofer Topological Relations family: If all four intersections among all object parts are empty, then the two objects are disjoint. (https://doi.org/10.1007/3-540-51295-0_148 Definition 1)
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: disjoint

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: To forward or supply a resource to a third-party.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: distribute
owl:NamedIndividual.skos:note: This action is always evaluated at the consumer side and allows it to become a data provider of this resource.

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: If a temporal entity T1 has the same duration as another temporal entity T2, then their length or their duration is equal. Instants and xsd:dateTimeStamp Literals have always the duration 'P0Y0M0DT0H0M0S'^^xsd:duration and therefore have always the same duration.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: has same duration
owl:NamedIndividual.skos:note: Compares an instance of ids:TemporalEntity with an instance of ids:TemporalEntity.

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: If a TemporalEntity T1 is during another TemporalEntity T2, then the beginning of T1 is after the beginning of T2, and the end of T1 is before the end of T2.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: during
owl:NamedIndividual.skos:note: Compares an instance of ids:Instant, ids:Interval or xsd:dateTimeStamp with an instance of ids:Interval. Evaluates to false if compared to a non ids:Interval.

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: A continuous elapsed time period which may be used for exercising of the action of the Rule. Allowed operators are idsc:SHORTER, idsc:SHORTER_EQ, idsc:LONGER, idsc:LONGER_EQ, and idsc:DURATION_EQ with datatype xsd:duration.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: elapsed time

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: The data artifact or parts of it are encrypted and can not be read by neither the ids:DataConsumer nor any other third party. The encryption algorithm might be specified by a constraint.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: ecrypt
owl:NamedIndividual.skos:note: This action is always evaluated at the provider side.

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: The artifact is encrypted so the data itself cannot be read by any user without having the corresponding key.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: is encrypted

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Remote target for an action or information provider (PIP). Must be used together with idsc:IS or idsc:IN operators. RightOperand must be a xsd:anyURI or an URL which should point to an actually deployed endpoint. An example is a refinment of idsc:NOTIFY where idsc:REMOTE points to a Clearing House.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: endpoint

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Arithmetic equals operator (5 = 5).
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: equals

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Logical equals operator (true = true).
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: equals

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: The feature dimension regarding whether current events are happening. Does NOT refer 'events' as in real-time data, sensor observations, or Complex Event Processing but rather as 'World Cup 2018' or 'Hannover Trade Fair'.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: current event

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: If an interval T1 is finished by another interval T2, then the beginning of T1 is before the beginning of T2, and the end of T1 is coincident with the end of T2.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: finished by
owl:NamedIndividual.skos:note: Compares an instance of ids:Interval to another instance of ids:Interval. Evaluates to false if compared to a non ids:Interval or one interval is empty.

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: If an Interval T1 finishes another interval T2, then the beginning of T1 is after the beginning of T2, and the end of T1 is coincident with the end of T2.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: finishes
owl:NamedIndividual.skos:note: Compares an instance of ids:Interval to another instance of ids:Interval. Evaluates to false if compared to a non ids:Interval or one interval is empty.

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: To grant use of a resource to another party. Does *not* imply any other usage rights.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: grant use
owl:NamedIndividual.skos:note: This action is always evaluated at the consumer side, at the moment a third party intends to access the resource as received by the original consumer.

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Greater-than operator. Can be used for numeric (5 idsc:GT 2) comparisons.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: greater than

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Greater-than-or-equals operator. Can be used for numeric (5 idsc:GTEQ 2) comparisons.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: greater than or equals

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: If a user has a specific membership required for accessing a resource. A membership includes always a role and a related organisation (see also org:). Should be used together with a RightOperand pointing to an accessible endpoint providing this information.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: has Member

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: If a user needs to be located at a certain site required for accessing a resource. A 'HAS_SITE' relation includes always a membership (role and related organisation) corresponding to the site. Should be used together with a RightOperand pointing to an accessible endpoint providing this information.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: has site

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Operator examining if the target resource has a certain state at the moment, for instance is anonymized (idsc:ANONYMIZED).
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: has state

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Every IDS Connector is in the intended audience for the DAT with this 'scope' property.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: all IDS Connectors

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Element-of operator. Allowed RightOperands are RDF collections('(A B C)').
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: in

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Endpoint is used for data input.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Input endpoint

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Spatial operator 'inside' as defined by the Egenhofer Topological Relations family: An object A is inside of another object B if (1) A and B share interior, but not bounding faces, (2) if A has bounding faces which are interior faces of B, and (3) none of B's bounding faces coincides with any of A's interior faces. (https://doi.org/10.1007/3-540-51295-0_148 Definition 4)
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: inside
owl:NamedIndividual.skos:note: In addition, a point is inside a polygom iff the point is in the polygom's interior (the point itself has no interior).

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Is satisfied if a system is inside a specified target network or network range.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: inside network
Integrity Verification Scope Kernel Core Container
Integrity Verification Scope Kernel Core Container Application

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Formal, machine-interpretable definition of a protocol-specific API, e.g. OpenAPI, GraphQL, API Blueprint, WSDL.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Interface definition

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: The message recipient encountered an internal error while processing the message (e.g., storage capacity exceeded).
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: INTERNAL_RECIPIENT_ERROR

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: The event occurs at uneven intervals.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Irregular

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: To log information or store information about incidents in a local file or database. Is not necessarily available to external parties but can be used to create transparency on happened events.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: log
owl:NamedIndividual.skos:note: This action is always evaluated at the consumer side.

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: If a temporal entity T1 is longer than another temporal entity T2, then the length or duration of T1 is bigger. Instants and xsd:dateTimeStamp Literals have always the duration 'P0Y0M0DT0H0M0S'^^xsd:duration and therefore have always the same duration.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: longer
owl:NamedIndividual.skos:note: Compares an instance of ids:TemporalEntity with an instance of xsd:duration.

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: If temporal entity T1 is longer or equals than another temporal entity T2, then the length or duration of T1 is bigger or their length or their duration is equal. Instants and xsd:dateTimeStamp Literals have always the duration 'P0Y0M0DT0H0M0S'^^xsd:duration and therefore have always the same duration.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: longer or equals
owl:NamedIndividual.skos:note: Compares an instance of ids:TemporalEntity with an instance of xsd:duration.

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Less-than operator. Can be used for numeric (2 idsc:LT 5) comparisons.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Lithuanian
less than
owl:NamedIndividual.skos:note: Do not confuse with idsc:LT (which is a language).

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Less-than-or-equals operator. Can be used for numeric (2 idsc:LTEQ 5) comparisons.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: less than or equals

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: The originating message is malformed or missing information.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: MALFORMED_MESSAGE

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Regex operator for strings. Evaluates to true iff the regex pattern of the RightOperand matches the LeftOperand.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: matches

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: If a TemporalEntity or (xsd:dateTimeStamp Literal) T1 meets another TemporalEntity (or xsd:dateTimeStamp Literal) T2, then the end of T1 is coincident with the beginning of T2.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: meets
owl:NamedIndividual.skos:note: Compares an instance of TemporalEntity or xsd:dateTimeStamp Literal to another instance of TemporalEntity or xsd:dateTimeStamp Literal. Evaluates to true if T1 or T2 are Instants (or xsd:dateTimeStamp Literal) and the condition in the comment holds.

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: If a user is part of a certain organisation required for accessing a resource. Should be used together with a RightOperand pointing to an accessible endpoint providing this information.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: memberOf

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: The sender of the rejection does not support the incoming message type (e.g., ids:QueryMessage).
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: MESSAGE_TYPE_NOT_SUPPORTED

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: The sender of the rejection does not implement a certain functionality stated in the message (e.g., query language).
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: METHOD_NOT_SUPPORTED

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: If a TemporalEntity or (xsd:dateTimeStamp Literal) T1 is met by another TemporalEntity or (xsd:dateTimeStamp Literal) T2, then the beginning of T1 is coincident with the end of T2.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: met by
owl:NamedIndividual.skos:note: Compares an instance of TemporalEntity (or xsd:dateTimeStamp Literal) to another instance of TemporalEntity (or xsd:dateTimeStamp Literal). Evaluates to true if T1 or T2 are Instants (or xsd:dateTimeStamp Literal) and the condition in the comment holds.

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Minimal logging.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Minimal Logging

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: To change a resource locally.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: modify
owl:NamedIndividual.skos:note: This action is always evaluated at the consumer side. It corresponds to 'allow changes of the copied resource'.

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: The event occurs once a month.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Monthly

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Code indicates that several languages are used or no concrete language can be determined.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Multilingual

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: To forward the resource under the same policy. Implies a permission to distribute.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: next policy
owl:NamedIndividual.skos:note: This action is always evaluated at the consumer side.

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Logical difference operator (false != true).
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: not equals

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: To log information or notify an instance about incidents. Can be used to define Clearing House interactions.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: notify
owl:NamedIndividual.skos:note: This action can target the consumer and the data provider of the resource.

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Authenticity of a message sender has failed or is not verifiable.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: NOT_AUTHENTICATED

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Sender is not authorized to initiate the command.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: NOT_AUTHORIZED

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Requested Resource was not found.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: NOT_FOUND

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: No logging.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: No Logging

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: OAUTH2 via JWT
Endpoint is used for data output.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Output endpoint

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: If a interval T1 is overlapped another proper interval T2, then the beginning of T1 is before the beginning of T2, the end of T1 is after the beginning of T2, and the end of T1 is before the end of T2.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: overlapped by
owl:NamedIndividual.skos:note: Compares an instance of ids:Interval to another instance of ids:Interval. Evaluates to false if compared to a non ids:Interval or one interval is empty.

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: If an ids:Interval T1 overlapps another ids:Interval T2, then the beginning of T1 is after the beginning of T2, the beginning of T1 is before the end of T2, and the end of T1 is after the end of T2.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: overlaps
owl:NamedIndividual.skos:note: Compares an instance of ids:Interval to another instance of ids:Interval. Evaluates to false if compared to a non ids:Interval or one interval is empty.

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: path to attribute

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Monetary payment, without any further sepcification on the type, amount or purpose.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: payment

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Monetary amount to pay, usually used with idsc:EQ. Datatype is double. Currency required.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: payAmount

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: The current system time (as UTC xsd:dateTimeStamp) for evaluating a time-related constraint. Allowed operators are idsc:AFTER, idsc:BEFORE, idsc:CONTAINS, idsc:TEMPORAL_DISJOINT, idsc:DURING, idsc:TEMPORAL_EQUALS, idsc:FINISHED_BY, idsc:FINISHES, idsc:MEETS, idsc:MET_BY, idsc:OVERLAPS, idsc:OVERLAPPED_BY, idsc:STARTS, idsc:STARTED_BY and idsc:DURATION_EQ with RightOperand ids:TemporalEntity.

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Endpoint is used to start (or control) app processing.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Process endpoint

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Indicates that a Connector is deployed for productive use.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Productive Deployment

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: The artifact is pseudo pseudonymized.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: is pseudonymized

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: A defined purpose for exercising the action of the Rule. Use with idsc:IN or idsc:SAME_AS and RDF Resources.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: purpose

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Quantity limitation for exercising the action of the Rule. Operators can be idsc:LT, idsc:LTEQ, idsc:EQ, idsc:GT, idsc:GTEQ. Datatype is xsd:double.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: quantity

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: The event occurs every three months.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Quarterly

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: To obtain data from the resource.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: read
owl:NamedIndividual.skos:note: This action is always evaluated at the provider side. It corresponds to 'give access to a resource'.

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: The limit how often exercising the action of the Rule may be possible. Operators can be idsc:LT, idsc:LTEQ, idsc:EQ, idsc:GT, idsc:GTEQ. Datatype is xsd:double.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: recurrence rate

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: A generic template for policy requests with one permission and several constraints
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Policy Request Template
owl:NamedIndividual.skos:note: The <Consumer Participant URI> asks <Provider Participant URI> to [ids:use|ids:read|...] its [<Representation URI>|<Artifact URI>]. owl:NamedIndividual.skos:note: A owl:sameAs A is always true.

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Formal, machine-interpretable definition of a data schema, e.g. XMLSchema, JSONSchema
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Schema definition

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: The security level the consuming connector must have. Use together with idsc:SAME_AS or idsc:IN. The value decides which attribute dimension is regarded.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: security level

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: The event occurs twice a year.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Semiannual

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: The event occurs twice a month.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Semimonthly

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: The event occurs twice a week.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Semiweekly

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: If a temporal entity T1 is shorter than another temporal entity T2, then the length or duration of T1 is shorter. Instants and xsd:dateTimeStamp Literals have always the duration 'P0Y0M0DT0H0M0S'^^xsd:duration and therefore have always the same duration.

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: If a temporal entity T1 is shorter or equals than another temporal entity T2, then the length or duration of T1 is shorter or their length or their duration is equal. Instants and xsd:dateTimeStamp Literals have always the duration 'P0Y0M0DT0H0M0S'^^xsd:duration and therefore have always the same duration.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: shorter or equals
owl:NamedIndividual.skos:note: Compares an instance of ids:TemporalEntity with an instance of xsd:duration.

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Spatial operator 'contains' as defined by the Egenhofer Topological Relations family: An object A contains another object B if A and B share interior but no bounding faces; if B has bounding faces which are interior faces of , and none of A's bounding faces coincides with any of B's interior faces. (https://doi.org/10.1007/3-540-51295-0_148 Definition 5)
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: contains
owl:NamedIndividual.skos:note: In addition, a polygom contains a point iff the point is in the polygom's interior (the point itself has no interior).

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Spatial operator 'equals' as defined by the Egenhofer Topological Relations family: Two objects are equal if both intersections of bounding and interior faces are not empty while the two boundary-interior intersections are empty. (https://doi.org/10.1007/3-540-51295-0_148 Definition 3)
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: equals
owl:NamedIndividual.skos:note: In addition, two spatial points are equal iff both coordinates are equal (points have no interior).

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Spatial operator 'meet' as defined by the Egenhofer Topological Relations family: If the intersection among the bounding faces is not empty, whereas all other 3 intersections are empty, then the two objects meet. (https://doi.org/10.1007/3-540-51295-0_148 Definition 2)
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: meet

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Spatial operator 'overlap' as defined by the Egenhofer Topological Relations family: Two objects overlap if they have common interior faces and the bounding faces have common parts with the opposite interior faces. (https://doi.org/10.1007/3-540-51295-0_148 Definition 8)
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: overlap

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: If a TemporalEntity T1 is started by another proper interval T2, then the beginning of T1 is coincident with the beginning of T2, and the end of T1 is after the end of T2.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: started by
owl:NamedIndividual.skos:note: Compares an instance of TemporalEntity (or xsd:dateTimeStamp Literal) to instance of ids:Interval. Evaluates to false if T1 is an Instant (or xsd:dateTimeStamp Literal) as the end of T1 can then not be idsc:AFTER the end of T2.

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: If an interval T1 starts with a TemporalEntity T2, then the beginning of T1 is coincident with the beginning of T2, and the end of T1 is before the end of T2.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: starts
owl:NamedIndividual.skos:note: Compares an instance of ids:Interval to another instance of TemporalEntity (or xsd:dateTimeStamp Literal). Evaluates to false if T2 is not an ids:Interval as then the end of T1 can never be idsc:BEFORE the end of T2

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Specifies whether an (external) resource is true/false, active/inactive, has happened/not happened, etc. Operator must be idsc:EQUALS with RightOperands of datatype xsd:anyURI. The referenced URI should point to a (remote) resource which returns a xsd:boolean value.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: state

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Equals operator for strings. Evaluates to true iff all characters and their sequence is the same.

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Contained in operator for strings. Evaluates to true iff the LeftOperand is contained completely by the RightOperand.

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Execution system or execution environment that is used to access the asset under consideration, usually an IDS Connector. The regarded data object should correspond to the IDS Connector class and its attributes. Must be used together with idsc:SAME_AS, idsc:NOT, idsc:HAS_STATE, idsc:IN, idsc:COVERED_BY idsc:INSIDE, idsc:SPATIAL_EQUALS, idsc:DISJOINT, or idsc:INSIDE_NETWORK operators. RightOperandReference must be a URI identifying the target system(s).

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: If a TemporalEntity (or xsd:dateTimeStamp) T1 is disjoint with another ids:TemporalEntity (or xsd:dateTimeStamp) T2, then T1 is idsc:BEFORE or idsc:AFTER to T2.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: disjoint
owl:NamedIndividual.skos:note: Compares an instance of ids:TemporalEntity or xsd:dateTimeStamp Literal to an instance of ids:TemporalEntity or xsd:dateTimeStamp Literal.

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: If a TemporalEntity (or xsd:dateTimeStamp Literal) T1 is equals another TemporalEntity (or xsd:dateTimeStamp Literal) T2, then the beginning of T1 is coincident with the beginning of T2, and the end of T1 is coincident with the end of T2. The beginning and ending is the same for instances of ids:Instant (or xsd:dateTimeStamp Literal).
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: interval equals
owl:NamedIndividual.skos:note: Compares an instance of TemporalEntity or xsd:dateTimeStamp Literal to another TemporalEntity or xsd:dateTimeStamp. Evaluates to false if a DurationEntity is involved.
